  "caveats": [
    "entropy_per_action_mean at collapsed checkpoints (~1e13) is a numerical artifact: with scale at the 1e-6 actor_min_std floor, log_prob of a clipped tanh sample (arctanh at |a|=1-1e-6) explodes; the scale_median series is the clean evidence.",
    "Collapse timing is bounded by eval cadence (~10.5k): saturation>0.5 and logits_gap>20 both first appear at the 21k eval, i.e. collapse completed within ~10k steps of learning onset (warmup ends at 10k); finer ordering vs critic-gap growth is not resolvable from saved metrics.",
    "Stochastic==deterministic at early/mid/final is the expected signature of total collapse (sigma=1e-6 floor), not evidence against the hypothesis; the init checkpoint shows what entropy provided (path 20.0m vs 0.9m, 18 vs 2 cells)."
  ]
